The Phoenix Rooivalk system implements a sophisticated counter-drone defense platform with three core business domains:

## 1. Threat Response System (Importance: 95/100)
- Multi-layered threat detection with AI-based classification
- Autonomous response selection based on threat characteristics
- Dynamic formation management for defensive deployments
- Real-time tactical adjustments based on threat behavior
- Integration with military-grade sensor fusion systems

Key Files:
- `apps/threat-simulator-desktop/src/game/engine.rs`
- `apps/threat-simulator-desktop/src/game/formations.rs`
- `apps/threat-simulator-desktop/src/game/weapons.rs`

## 2. Evidence Management System (Importance: 90/100)
- Dual-chain anchoring for evidence records (Solana + EtherLink)
- Tamper-proof audit trails for all countermeasure deployments
- Complex job management with exponential backoff retry logic
- Automated confirmation polling across multiple blockchains

Key Files:
- `apps/api/src/repository.rs`
- `crates/anchor-etherlink/src/lib.rs`
- `crates/anchor-solana/src/lib.rs`

## 3. Tactical Simulation Engine (Importance: 85/100)
- Progressive difficulty scaling with 7 distinct threat types
- Complex weapon synergy system with multiplicative effects
- Resource management with thermal and energy constraints
- Formation-based tactical advantage calculations

Key Files:
- `apps/marketing/src/components/utils/responseProtocols.ts`
- `apps/marketing/src/components/utils/strategicDeployment.ts`

## 4. Research & Development System (Importance: 80/100)
- Technology tree with interdependent unlocks
- Performance-based progression system
- Compliance-aware weapon system deployment
- Real-world inspired countermeasure development paths

The system emphasizes military-grade defensive capabilities while maintaining strict compliance requirements and evidence tracking. Core business logic focuses on threat response automation, tactical deployment optimization, and comprehensive audit trails.

